# Release publish sequencing (do not invert)

## When this rule attaches (Cursor)

**Context:** **`alwaysApply: false`** — loads when a path matches the **`globs`** above **or** the operator types the English session token **`release-ritual`** **or** attaches **`@release-publish-sequencing.mdc`**. **`docker-local-smoke-cleanup.mdc`** stays **`alwaysApply: true`** for **smoke / prune / disk** hygiene on the dev workstation; this rule carries the **full** **tag → GitHub → Docker → Hub copy → `PUBLISHED_SYNC`** order.

**Companion:** Session **`release-ritual`** (see **`session-mode-keywords.mdc`**) and **`docs/ops/OPERATOR_AGENT_COLD_START_LADDER.md`** § *Token → rule latch (`release-ritual`)* — use **`@release-publish-sequencing.mdc`** in **fresh** threads when you are **shipping a semver** but no globbed file is open yet.

**Rollback:** `git revert` the commit that flipped this rule or `git show <parent>:.cursor/rules/release-publish-sequencing.mdc`.

**Problem:** Assistants (and rushed humans) stack a **pre-release** bump (`X.Y.Z-beta`) or the **next** dev version on `main` **before** **Git tag**, **GitHub Release**, and **Docker Hub** are real. That makes **`vX.Y.Z`** ambiguous, breaks “tag this commit,” and confuses **published** vs **working** version across **GitHub**, **Hub**, and **README**. A second failure mode is **pushing Hub images without a local smoke** on **Docker Desktop** (or without **disk headroom**), then **never pruning** — leaving **many** `data_boar:*` / `fabioleitao/data_boar:*` tags and stopped containers on the **primary Windows dev workstation**.

**Canonical prose + checklist:** **`docs/VERSIONING.md`** (working vs published, bump list, distribution). **Per-release commands:** **`docs/releases/X.Y.Z.md`**, **`docs/ops/DOCKER_IMAGE_RELEASE_ORDER.md`**, **`docs/ops/DOCKER_HUB_REPOSITORY_DESCRIPTION.md`**. **Local Docker hygiene:** **`.cursor/rules/docker-local-smoke-cleanup.mdc`** (**always-on**), **`.cursor/skills/docker-smoke-container-hygiene/SKILL.md`**, **`scripts/docker/README.md`**.

---

## When this applies

- Any request to **ship**, **publish**, **cut a release**, **tag**, or **bump version** for **public** consumers.
- Before saying “release is done” or “published on all networks.”

---

## Mandatory order (strict)

Do **not** claim a version is **published** until **all** relevant steps for **that** semver are done. **Typical** sequence:

1. **`main` (or release branch merged to `main`)** contains **`pyproject.toml` `version = "X.Y.Z"`** with **no** `-beta`/`-rc` suffix for **that** publish — unless the project explicitly ships only pre-releases (not this repo’s default for “public release”).
2. **Git tag:** `vX.Y.Z` on the **exact commit** that still has **`X.Y.Z` final** in `pyproject.toml`. If there are **two** commits (release, then beta), the tag **must** point to the **release** commit, **not** `HEAD` with beta.
3. **Push tag:** `git push origin vX.Y.Z` (or project remote).
4. **GitHub Release:** `gh release create vX.Y.Z` with notes from **`docs/releases/X.Y.Z.md`** (or equivalent). **Verify** with `gh release list` / `gh release view vX.Y.Z` in-session — **do not** invent “it’s live” without a check when tools work.
4b. **Post-release map integrity (`.postN` only):** when preparing **`docs/releases/X.Y.Z.postN.md`**, the **Mandatory map** must enumerate each **unpublished** `maturity_build` between the previous published post and this one (for example `.212` … `.225` before **`post4=.226`** — `.225` is the last *unpublished fix* row; the **published** post4 upload is **`.226`**, which is the `N` baseline per ADR-0073) using explicit rows `*(fix, unpublished on PyPI)*`. Do not collapse this interval into a single summary line.
4c. **Notes style vs proof appendix:** in the Mandatory map, the **Notes** column must be **short effect prose** (what changed for the user/operator) with `#issue` when known — never raw `fix(...)` commit subjects. Keep git-literal evidence (subjects + hashes) only in a dedicated **Appendix — Fix set (N=...)** section below.
5. **PyPI (OIDC dispatch — zero workstation token; ADR-0031 packaging + ADR-0005 workflow pins):**
   1. **TestPyPI:** `.\scripts\pypi-publish.ps1 -Target testpypi` (Linux/macOS: `./scripts/pypi-publish.sh -t testpypi`) — dispatches **`.github/workflows/publish-pypi.yml`**. **No** `UV_PUBLISH_TOKEN`; **no** local `uv publish`.
   2. **Verify TestPyPI:** `gh run watch` (after `gh run list --workflow=publish-pypi.yml`), confirm **`https://test.pypi.org/project/data-boar/`** shows the expected version; optional `pip install -i https://test.pypi.org/simple/ data-boar==X.Y.Z`.
   3. **Production PyPI:** when TestPyPI is good and the release gate is satisfied, `.\scripts\pypi-publish.ps1 -Target pypi` (or `./scripts/pypi-publish.sh -t pypi`).
   4. **Verify PyPI:** **`https://pypi.org/project/data-boar/`** — optional `pipx install data-boar==X.Y.Z` smoke on a lab host.
6. **Docker image — build, smoke, push, prune, Hub UI (see also [`docs/ops/DOCKER_IMAGE_RELEASE_ORDER.md`](../../docs/ops/DOCKER_IMAGE_RELEASE_ORDER.md)):**
   1. **Disk (primary dev PC):** Before a large `docker build`, confirm **free space** on the volume Docker uses (Windows: e.g. `Get-PSDrive C` / relevant drive; Docker Desktop **Settings → Resources** for disk location). Full disks cause **opaque build failures** and image corruption.
   2. **Build:** From repo root at the release commit, **`.\scripts\docker-lab-build.ps1`** (or the publish script’s build step) so the image embeds the same **`pyproject.toml`** as **`X.Y.Z`**.
   3. **Smoke on Docker Desktop (mandatory before `docker push` to Hub):** Run **`.\scripts\docker-image-smoke.ps1`** (or `docker run --rm` smoke) against the local image (e.g. **`data_boar:lab`**) per **`docs/DOCKER_SETUP.md`** §7. **Do not** push if smoke fails.
   3b. **Grype gate (#1028):** **`.\scripts\grype-image-gate.ps1 -Image data_boar:lab`** — **`--fail-on high --only-fixed`** + **`.grype.yaml`**; fails only on actionable High/Critical (never drop **`--only-fixed`**).
   4. **Push:** `docker login` + push **`fabioleitao/data_boar:X.Y.Z`** and **`latest`** per **`docs/ops/DOCKER_IMAGE_RELEASE_ORDER.md`** / **`docker-hub-publish.ps1`** when present.
   5. **Prune (same workstation):** **`.\scripts\docker-prune-local.ps1 -WhatIf`** then without **`-WhatIf`** — avoids **dozens** of stale **`data_boar:*`** tags cluttering Docker Desktop; align with **`docs/ops/BRANCH_AND_DOCKER_CLEANUP.md`** §4. Optional: `docker image prune -f` / `docker builder prune -f` when disk is tight — **confirm** with operator before aggressive prunes.
   6. **Hub repository page:** Paste **Short + Full** from **`docs/ops/DOCKER_HUB_REPOSITORY_DESCRIPTION.md`** (replace **entire** Full description). **Stable** releases only for this marketing refresh; **`-beta`** / **`-rc`** do not require Hub page text updates unless asked. **Same-session rule:** If you **push** any **customer-pullable** tag (including hygiene tags like **`v1.7.2-safe`**) or **delete** Hub tags, refresh Hub copy **in that session** so **Supported tags** / example **`docker tag`** lines match the **Tags** tab — never leave the overview citing **removed** tags (e.g. old **1.6.x**).
7. **Reconciliation:** **`docs/ops/today-mode/PUBLISHED_SYNC.md`** (+ **`.pt_BR.md`**) aligned with **published** semver, Hub tags, PyPI project page, and **`pyproject.toml` on `main`** (often **pre-release** after step 8).

**Only after** the operator (or automation with credentials) has completed the publish steps they care about:

8. **Separate commit** on `main`: bump working tree to **`X.Y.(Z+1)-beta`** (or next planned pre-release) + docs that distinguish **Current release** (README) vs **`main`**.

---

## Anti-patterns (never)

- **Do not** add **`X.Y.Z-beta`** on `main` in the **same** PR as the final **`X.Y.Z`** **before** tag + GitHub Release + Hub steps are **actually done**, unless the operator explicitly orders a **rebase/split** workflow and names the **SHA** to tag.
- **Do not** tell the operator the release is on GitHub because “the commits exist locally” — **verify** `origin` and **`gh`**.
- **Do not** tag **`vX.Y.Z`** on a commit whose **`pyproject.toml`** already says **`beta`** for the **next** line of work.
- **Do not** treat **Docker Hub push** as complete for a **stable** release **without** a **local smoke** on the operator **Docker Desktop** (or an explicit waiver, e.g. CI-only image) — see step **6.3**.
- **Do not** use **`UV_PUBLISH_TOKEN`** or local **`uv publish`** for maintainer PyPI uploads — use **`scripts/pypi-publish.ps1`** / **`pypi-publish.sh`** (OIDC dispatch only; #1046).
- **Do not** omit **prune** guidance after publish when many **`data_boar:*`** / **`fabioleitao/data_boar:*`** tags accumulate — use **`.\scripts\docker-prune-local.ps1`** per **`scripts/docker/README.md`**.
- **Do not** finish a Hub **push** or **tag cleanup** without updating **Docker Hub → Repository → General → Full description** when the old text still lists **tags that no longer exist** on Hub — that confuses pullers more than a missing paragraph.

---

## Mental model (one sentence)

**Published = tag + GitHub Release + PyPI (TestPyPI then production via OIDC dispatch) + Docker Hub image (+ local smoke before push) + Hub page copy + prune habit; working = what `pyproject.toml` says on `main` after you intentionally move forward.**

Session keyword **`release-ritual`**: **`read_file`** this rule (or **`@release-publish-sequencing.mdc`** if situational globs did not attach it), **`docs/VERSIONING.md`**, and **`.cursor/rules/docker-local-smoke-cleanup.mdc`** before editing versions, release docs, or advising Docker publish.
